Dialogs.Dialog: (I know！ I should invite you to the Hakone trip I won...)
Actually, I won it again！ I won a trip！
Rinko
Hmm...
Hey, what's wrong, ▲小早川＊▲？
I'm getting more and more worried about you, you know？
Maybe it's the hackers that have been making the rounds lately, or something like that...
For me？ No way...
Then that's fine. So？ Now, Atami？ Nikko/Kinugawa？
This time, Hakone！ Rediscovering the domestic honeymoon, two days and one night――
Wait, honey... what！？
It's a trip called "Rediscovering Domestic Honeymoon, 2 days and 1 night", you know？
Honeymoon... well, you know what that means, right？
Newlyweeds, right？ Back in the 1950s, the chosen locations were Hakone and Atami.
It seems to be a package deal for couples who want to visit such places again.
Heh... I see.
Not too keen on it？ Don't you wanna go to Hakone？
Hakone is fine, but... look...
What is the honeymoon part？
Even Rinko thinks about it... is it because of her age？
But, well, just because it's called that, it's no different than any other trip we've taken, right？
You know, ▲主人公＊▲...
Yeah.
We should go... to where we were talking before. You know, the trip.
Hakone, a domestic honey――
You don't have to say it all！
...just a trip, right？ Themed, right？
Yeah！ You're overthinking it, aren't you?？
Yeah, I guess so...
Well, I guess we'll go...
All right！
And then？ When are we going to do it？
(Let's see, I should set a date for a free day...)
Honeymoon for two days and one night, starting on ▲月▲▲日▲！
I already told you it's not that！
The name of the trip？
That kind of thing. But, well, maybe a little bit...
I'm not dating, okay？ It's like playing newlyweds... Rinko's not an ogre, either.
(Yay！！ We are playing honeymoon soon, ▲小早川＊▲！)
(I know！ I should invite you to the Hakone trip I won again...)
You know, ▲小早川＊▲.
Rinko
Hmm？
Actually, I won again, rediscovering the domestic honeymoon, two days and one night in Hakone！
Here it comes...
What is it？
I thought it was about time it came, cycle-wise.
Cycle？
That's it, right？ What do you call those holes in the firewall system？
You're still saying that... don't worry. I won it fair and square.
I'll leave it at that. Rinko is prepared to be an accomplice, too.
What are you gonna do？ We're going, right？
That's, well, I'll go, but I don't know what to do... like the last time, you know.
Oh, playing newlyweds？
Yeah... Actually, you know, I'm going to be so embarrassed later...
Well, take it easy. So, when do you want to do it？
(I should set a date for our honeymoon...)
Then. We'll be traveling to Hakone for two days and one night starting on the, ▲月▲▲日▲！
For our honeymoon, right？
What, are you sure？ We're just playing newlyweds, yeah？
Rinko is not an ogre, okay？ And I want to live up to my boyfriend's expectations, you know？
If we're going to do it or not, well... want to do it？
(You really want to do it, ▲小早川＊▲...)
(Yay！！We are playing honeymoon soon, ▲小早川＊▲！)
(My phone... Ah, it's ▲小早川＊▲.)
Yes, hello.
Rinko
Hello, this is Rinko.
What's the matter, ▲小早川＊▲？
You're free, right？
Well, I'm free.
You know, we're going to Hakone, right？
Ah, rediscovering the domestic honeymoon, a two day and one night trip to Hakone？
...Well, that's the thing.
We're going shopping now, okay？
(Anyway, let's go there.)
What's up？ Do you need to go shopping？ You're a well-traveled girl, aren't you, ▲小早川＊▲？
That's besides the point. This time, you see... it's that.
Hakone？
Not that one, you see... the other thing.
Honeymoon？
Well, that's what I'm talking about...
But we're just playing... so is it really necessary？
Think about that. You're older.
Hmm...
As I thought, no. I can't think of anything...
Rinko too. The only thing I could think of was potato chips.
That's buying for a school trip, though, right？
Well, I guess. Hmm... so there isn't？ Kinda looks like we're matching.
Like a pair？
I'll pretend I didn't hear that. Then what？ It's a game of communication, a game where we fight together.
Not very honeymoon-like...
Hah... enough already, stop it, okay？
Well, no need to force yourself to shop, right？
Maybe？ Oh, yeah！ Rinko, you know, has some shopping to do, so stay here.
Want me to go with you？ What are you buying？
That's is... you know... the feelings of something new for a bride to have, and...
Huh？
It's fine！ You don't have to know！ See you, okay？
(And there she hoes... I'll go back home...)
(You haven't arrived yet, ▲小早川＊▲？)
Rinko
▲主人公＊▲.
You were already here, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Um... well, yeah？ It was hot and humid this morning, you know？ And, you see...
You can't oversleep as newlyweds, can you？
Huh？ ...Are you sure about that？
Rinko
You're late！ Ugh... so cold！
Right on time, huh？ You're here that early？
Because it's――
Like, you can't oversleep as newlyweds？
Huh？ ...Are you sure about that？
Rinko
In case you're wondering... that's how it's set up, and it's not a matter of feelings...
I see... okay！ Here we go, honeymoon！
Hey, wait！ Don't be so obvious！
Rinko
Hmm... Rinko's imagination has its limits, you know？
What is it？
This train doesn't look like one, no matter how you look at it.
"Like one"？ Ah, you mean for the honeymoon――
Keep your voice down！
(Are you in a good mood, ▲小早川＊▲？)
Ah！ This one？ You want to ride this one？
Yes. The Romancecar.
Heh！ That's nice！
...and then？ Is it looking like the real thing？
Eh？ Yes... well, I guess？ Hehe.
Rinko
Hmm, I can't do it...
What's wrong？
Too ordinary... Not Honey nor Moon...
Yes, until the "Romancecar" comes, right？
That's right... I beg you, come "Romance Car"？
Oh, the "romancecar" still seems nice！
Yeah. First of all, it's a cool name, right？ Hehe！
All right, let's get in, shall we？
Yay！
The seats are so spacious！
Rinko
Nice！ What can I say, it's more open？
I guess？ Traveling makes people open up, right？
That's right～ yeah, that's why.
What's up？
I'm getting more and more in the mood for it. You know... for the honeymoon, right？
(Good girl！)
Hmm... I still like the express！
Rinko
Right？ After all, it's extraordinary, yes.
Honeymoon-ish？
Y-yeah... still, that keyword is no good.
Still, huh... When would be a good time？
Now, it'll be okay... geez, it's fine to say it, okay？ You know, honeymoon... like that？
(Hey, that's a little embarrassing...)
Rinko
Let me ask you a question.
What is it？
We've been riding through town for quite a while now, right？ Aboard this express, that is.
Unlike in Atami, we're riding on land.
Rinko
You know, unlike Atami, we didn't try it, right？ You know... playing.
Playing honeymoon？
Y-Yes, that's right, but... it's something different, this time.
Why would that be？
It is, after all, a matter of preparedness, or... the purpose of this trip, isn't it？
(Did it serve a purpose...)
Rinko
Right, speaking of Atami, we didn't like it, you know, "playing"...
Yeah... that happened.
This time, I'm going to make sure we do it right, okay？ You started this, remember？
(Make sure we "play honeymoon"... I'll do my best...)
Rinko
I see. I get my memories mixed up with Atami. I get it...
You and Rinko have traveled a lot in the past, don't we？
Yeah, I guess？
Rinko always likes the last trip we took the best. So I hope it will be the same this time.
PA system
We will soon arrive at the last stop, Hakone-Yumoto. For the Hakone Tozan Line and Gora direction...
Rinko
Did you hear？ It's Hakone- Yumoto！
Good！ Let's get ready to go！
Hah～！ We're here, in Hakone！
Rinko
Hey... actually, it's Rinko's first time in Hakone...
It's just like that, isn't it？ It's like "The Tourist Attraction"！ I see...
That's because we're in Hakone！ Let's go！
Ah, wait！
Hmm？
So, you and Rinko will be like that now, right？ You know, um...
Honeymoon？
Would you prefer it if I got closer to you than usual？
Ah, could you？
Honeymoon▼ Hehe.
(I'm happy, but a little embarrassed...)
Hah～！ Here we are again, Hakone！
Rinko
Here we are, Hakone！
That's why... ahem！
Hmm？
From here on out, I'm going to get into it, okay？ Into our honeymoon.
Me too. Come on, honeymoon！
Hehe▼ Honeymoon！
Rinko
Ah！ I can see the Red Bridge！
Oh, there it is...
Rinko
The Hydrangea Bridge, right？ Yeah... hmm, where are the hydrangeas？
Hydrangeas are... ah！ Look, they're blooming on the riverbank, right？
Hmm？ Where？ ...oh, I see them！ Good, good.
Rinko, you know, she'd like to refrain from being so snarky, at least on our honeymoon.
Rather than being a famous place for hydrangeas, Hakone is a town that welcomes tourists with hydrangeas――
I hear it's like a memorial to that, you know？
June in Hakone is hydrangea month, right？ Okay. I appreciate the gesture.
Ah, come on...
A "hydrangea bridge", huh.
Rinko
No hydrangeas, huh... Well, it's autumn, right？
Seems we are late, huh？
But you know, the autumn leaves are beautiful. It's a nice contrast to the green of the river.
It's true... You're kinda positive today, aren't you, ▲小早川＊▲？
I guess？ Rinko, you know, at least during our honeymoon, I'm not being cynical.
...will it last？
That's up to you... right, my husband？ Hehe▼
I know it's a little early, but do you want to go have lunch around here？ Because it's Hakone, so...
Rinko
Ramen？
...we're in Hakone, remember？
I want to eat ramen.
You don't waver in that regard... But is there any place around here that does ramen？
There is... maybe.
Ah, look！ There it is, right there！
Is there... Heh, Yumoto handmade ramen, "Haikara Chuka Nisshintei".
Here will do！ Come, let's go in！
Shopkeeper
Welcome！
Heh... kinda looks like a retro cafe, doesn't it？
There, you see, it's Hakone. It's not just a ramen shop.
I understand... Have you decided what you're going to ask for yet, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko's will... okay, this one！
Sorry to keep you waiting！ We will be serving your "Sanma-men" and your "Gomoku-wontan-men"！
Here it comes, hehe♪
It look delicious, doesn't it, ▲小早川＊▲？
Right？ Oh... you want me do it then？
Hmm？
This is the place, right？
Here, open wide～...
Thanks for the food！ Hah～... satisfied▼
I know it's a little early, but do you want to go have lunch？
Rinko
I agree！ Hakone is also known for...
Over here！ The handmade ramen "Haikara Nisshintei". Come, let's go in, okay？
So, what would you like today？
A "Sanma-men" and some "Chashu-men".
Both！？
Because we are two people, right？
Clerk
Thank you for your waiting. Here are "Sanma-men" and "Chashu-men".
Give me some pork♪
So that's what you meant...
Why not？ We're newlyweds. I'll give you some of Rinko's too, okay？
Here, open wide～...
Thanks for the food. I knew Hakone was the place for ramen♪
Rinko
Hey, are we taking the train again？ We're in Hakone, right？
We'll take the Hakone Tozan Railway to Gora. We're going to the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum".
A mountain railroad？ Heh！
You haven't read the itinerary at all...？
I'll take three steps back and follow you. I am a Japanese wife.
You climb mountains with this？ Looks so ordinary... I imagined it to be much more rugged.
It's the famous mountain climbing train, remember？ Come on, let's get on！
Rinko
Next up is the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum", right？
Yes. We will take the Hakone Tozan Railway to Gora.
There it is！ The mountain railroad！
Once you get on it, it makes you look tough, doesn't it？
Maybe？
Will you help me to finish today？ Rinko doesn't want to climb the mountain on her feet, okay？
Rinko
Hydrangeas！ Look, lots of blooms！
Yeah... This is beautiful...
It's amazing... running through the hydrangeas...
You said a lot of things in "Hydrangea Bridge," didn't you, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko was totally wrong... the hydrangeas of Hakone are nice...
(I'm glad you're having fun ▲小早川＊▲！)
Rinko
Look, autumn leaves. I like it...
Yeah... it's very autumnal, isn't it？
After all, it's autumn in Hakone...
Oh, that's kind of honest, isn't it？
It's fine, isn't it？ It's our honeymoon. Hehe.
Is that so？
There are honeymoons like this where you can enjoy the uniqueness of Japan, yes...
(I'm glad you like it. Nice time to be here, ▲小早川＊▲.)
We're here！ The last stop, Gora Station！
Rinko
Huh？ Isn't it kinda cool？
It's been quite a climb, huh？
Yeah, it was a climb！ The railroad really could do it, right？ It did its best.
Yeah. From here, we will take a bus to the "Hakone Glass Forest Museum".
Eh...？ Why don't we try a little harder on the mountain railroad...
I see, you're not very good with buses, are you？
Hmm？
In times like this, why don't you show off your masculinity？ It's your honeymoon.
You want to cross your arms？
Yeah, I'll do my best...
We're here！ The last stop, Gora Station！
Rinko
So cold！ How far up the mountain did the mountain railroad climb...
Now, now. It feels like Hakone, doesn't it？
It's cold～... let's hurry up and go someplace warm！
Want to take an early ride？ It's a bus to the "Hakone Glass Forest Art Museum".
That's right... uh... but, I have to get ready...
You're exaggerating...
In the meantime, you can hug me... That's also a husband's duty, too, you know？
Hehe... I'm ready to go.
Oh, it's quite a slope...
Rinko
Uh...
You're already tired, ▲小早川＊▲？
So much...
Hang in there, we're almost there！
The next bump may be a mountain...
Hey！ ――Oh！？
Ah...
...are you okay？
Yeah... I'll do my best now. Hehe.
Announcement
The next stop is in front of Tawaraseki/ Hakone Glass Forest Museum...
Announcement
This is the Tawaraseki and Hakone Glass Forest area. Please make sure not to forget anything when you get off...
Rinko
Good job for hanging on. Here we are, the Hakone Glass Forest Museum, ▲小早川＊▲.
Let me tell you, I've raised the bar considerably with the bus now, okay？ I expect to be entertained.
Hey look at that, huh？ A glass tree！
Oh, yeah. It's sparkling... Why is that？
Ticket Seller
Please take your time and enjoy.
Is this the ticket？ Heh... I like it！ I'm excited for it, okay？
Elaborate, right？
Announcement
This is the Tawaraseki and Hakone Glass Forest area. Please make sure not to forget anything when you get off...
Here we are. Hakone Glass Forest Museum！
Rinko
Hah～... I feel like this place is the reason I've been able to hang on.
See that, the crystal glass tree, sparkling today？
Oh, it's true. It's just sunlight, right？ So mysterious...
Yup. That's mysterious...
Ticket Seller
Please take your time and enjoy.
Huh？ This is different from the last time, isn't it？ Rinko wants to keep it again.
It's as elaborate as ever...
Rinko
Wow... this is amazing！ It was beyond Rinko's imagination...
The glass is amazing, but the inside of the museum, too, you know？ It's all inspired by Venice, you know？
Yeah... it has an European feel！ Over there, let's go？
Oh, look at this！ Glass hydrangeas！ Beautiful, isn't it？
Um, "Ortensia", huh. 2,000 pieces of crystal glass！？
2,000 pieces！？ Handmade, right？
I also hate the fact that they are lined up with real hydrangeas...
Look, what's this？ Japanese pampas grass？ It's all made of glass！
Pampas grass, huh... Let's see, it has 100 crystal glass ears！？
10,000 pieces... oh, they sway in the wind！ Such a nice work...
This is amazing, right？ It's a corridor of light！
9m high and 10m long. 160,000 crystal glasses！？
160,000！？ No wonder... It's so dazzling, with the sun reflecting off the glitter...
This, you know, you'd be remiss if you didn't take a photo of it, wouldn't you？
Okay！ Let's go in, ▲小早川＊▲！
You know, this place is kind of like an aisle, isn't it？
Yeah, it feels that way too, doesn't it？
Hehe▼ Should we walk through with our arms crossed？
Rinko
Hmm！ Nice, I knew it！ Especially after the bus！
Forget about it. That mountain in front of you, is that Owakudani？ You see the smoke？
Come, shall we？
Oh, look at this！ Glass hydrangeas！ Beautiful, isn't it？
Let's see, "Ortensia", huh. 2,000 pieces of crystal glass！？
2,000 pieces！？ Handmade, right？
I also hate the fact that they are lined up with real hydrangeas...
Look, what's this？ Japanese pampas grass？ It's all made of glass！
Pampas grass, huh... Let's see, it has 100 crystal glass ears！？
10,000 pieces... oh, they sway in the wind！ Such a nice work...
Depending on the sun, the glare makes my eyes flicker...
Oh... yeah, you want to take a photo？
Okay！
Now then, shall we do it？
Like the last time？
It's our honeymoon, right？ Dear▼ Wow, I'm really embarrassed...
"Venetian Glass Museum", huh.
Rinko
Heh... feels more like a mansion than an art museum, doesn't it？
Wow, it's so thin！ Mosaic？ It's not a painting, right？
"Millefiori"... means "thousand flowers". It is a technique that has been used since ancient Rome.
Ho... is it ancient Rome？ If you look closely, you can see all kinds of flowers... I bet they are expensive, aren't they？
"Goblet with a covered lid with dotted floral motifs". This is amazing...
Apparently it belonged to a European aristocrat, right？
I see... Okay, I've decided.
If Rinko were a thief, I'd take this.
Oh, look, they sell a lot of glass stuff. Let's take a look, shall we？
Okay, but don't bump it and drop it, okay？
I'm not a kid.
Heh... there's millefiori, too, you know？
Rinko
Fusing？ Heh, I heard you can experience it.
Wow, you combine glass and melt them together... Wanna give it a try？
I'll do it！
Hmm, it's done, but... the rest depends on how it's baked.
It seems to take a while to bake.
Do you want to take a break at a restaurant？
Rinko
Oh, you're so clever, aren't you？ You'll make a good husband, huh？ Hehe.
Oh, they're playing a canzone！
"Cafe Terrazza", huh... Sounds like an Italian cafe, right
Yeah...
What's up？
Singing, singing people, you think they'll come over here... and sing to us？
It'll be fine...
Clerk
Thank you for waiting. Here is your fruit tea.
Wow, look at this？ So much fruit！
Plenty of it, huh？
Mmm, smells sweet... just a little bit, doesn't it？ It's like a honeymoon. Hehe▼
Clerk
Yes, thank you for waiting. It turned out very nicely, didn't it？
Rinko
Thank you. Now... what is this？
Hmm... abstract？ It was supposed to be Rinko's face, but it looks like you.
There's still time to look around a little more, though.
Rinko
Great. Let's go over there, shall we？ Look, at the back of the garden.
Rinko
Wow, what is this, a glass fountain？ It's a Fontana！
Huh... it says there's 45,000 pieces of glass, huh.
As expected, I'm not really surprised by the number anymore... it's so shiny...
Hmm？ Look, over there, is that a bell？
The "Oath Bell", huh...
Ah, then, it's like that？ Like "Cape Aijo？
There doesn't seem to be any particular explanation for that...
But you know, this is picturesque, right？ A couple pulls from both ends, and they sound it.
Sounds nice... Do you want to make a oath？
Yeah. Then Rinko...
I better not tell you. I'll keep it a secret...
(Then, me and you, ▲小早川＊▲...)
"We'll get married！"
"We'll be together forever！"
"We're having a real honeymoon！"
Hehe, I made an oath...
Me too...
I bet we wished for the same... Because, you and Rinko, are on a honeymoon, right？
Rinko
Glass fountain！ Oh yeah, it's just down the road, right？
The "Oath Bell", right？ What are we doing today？
Hmm... yeah. Let's ring it. It's our honeymoon duty.
Have you decided what you're going to pledge？
(Okay then, me and you, ▲小早川＊▲...)
"Something for the trip！"
"A real honeymoon！"
Hehe▼ Same oath, right？
Ah... maybe.
Hmm？ Wait...
Rinko
Hah～... "Hakone Glass Forest Museum", huh.
Are you a little tired, ▲小早川＊▲？
I guess？ But, you know, it feels good.
I see. Nice place, huh？
Yeah, I want to come back. Oh, is the bus here？
Looks like it. Let's go, shall we？
Hmm...
Geez, are you feeling bad already！？
Not that, you know, that oath we did earlier. I'd like to know.
Oh... that one, huh？ Then you'll have to say it too, ▲小早川＊▲.
Huh？ Lemme see. Rinko's... come on, you get the general idea, right？
(What did you swear, ▲小早川＊▲？)
Announcement
Next, the last stop. Togendai, Togendai. Hakone ropeway, the sea...
Hey, this is Lake Ashi, right！
Yes it is！ It's a big place...
Do you want to take a walk？
Let's check in first. After this, we'll just stay at the hotel.
I-I see... I thought we were staying...
What's up？
What？ Nothing？ I just forgot this was supposed to be a honeymoon...
(When you say that, I get kind of nervous too...)
Look, I can see it now. The "Hakone Lake Hotel"！
Rinko
Heh... it looks like a resort.
Yeah, it's fashionable, right？
I see... Rinko was imagining something like a hot spring ryokan, so I'm a little nervous...
I should stay close with my husband...
Rinko
We're here！ The "Hakone Lake Hotel".
Are you still nervous？
Not at all？
I'm not scared because I'm with my husband▼ I said it, hehe▼
Rinko
Look at that... there's a chandelier...
It's true. This place looks European too, doesn't it？
Yeah... if Rinko was Alucard, I'd ride that chandelier.
Dracula, huh... Don't get on, okay？ Wait for me, I'm going to check in.
Yeah. Ah, wait――
What's up？
You know, it's our honeymoon. You want to put our names together？
(So that was it...)
Sorry to keep you waiting. I hope wrote it down as "▲苗字▲ Rinko".
Ah, yes...
Reception
Thank you so much for your patience. I will now give you an explanation of the facilities within the hotel.
Please come this way, madam.
Wha- yes！ Then, please.
Hehe... he thought of me as your wife. Did you see that？ Hehe▼
(I'm a little embarrassed too...)
Rinko
Oh yes, this one is the rideable chandelier！
Don't ride it, okay？ Okay, I'll go check in.
Ah, wait...
What's up？
You know what I mean, right？ You know, the name thing...
Sorry to keep you waiting. I hope wrote it down as "▲苗字▲ Rinko".
Ugh... I know, it's a little bit sneaky.
Reception
Thank you so much for your patience. I will now give you an explanation of the facilities within the hotel.
Please come this way, madam.
Ah, yes. Well, then, join me my husband.
I called you husband. Hehe... Geez, what was that？ What am I doing！
(You're confused, ▲小早川＊▲.)
Over here.
Rinko
Huh？ It's a Japanese-style room...
Oh, it's true.
Hah～... I'm kind of relieved...
I mean, it's a bit stuffy if it's too much like a honeymoon, isn't it？
You think so？
Of course, why wouldn't it be？ Because, you know, if you have a big bed with flower petals and stuff――
Ah！ Outside the window！ The mountains look so close～！
(Did you get nervous again？)
Rinko
You want a cup of tea？
Right, well――
Now, now, let your new wife Rinko do it for you.
Here you have it, go ahead. Dear▼
Oh, thank you.
Hehe♪
What's up？
Is it delicious？
Yeah.
It's nice, isn't it？ Like a married couple from the Showa era.
There is a porch, and the husband reads the newspaper or something and says, "Hey, tea！", like that.
Oh... that might be nice, huh？
Want to give it a try？ Say "hey".
Hey, tea！
...huh？ I don't know why, I'm kind of pissed off.
We still have some time before dinner, do you want to take a bath？
Rinko
Oh, sounds nice！ Dinner after a bath sounds so luxurious, doesn't it？
The men's bath is "Heaven" and the women's is "Sky"？ Oh, and there's an open-air bath？
Hmm？
That's troublesome... being separated... you know, being newlyweds and all that, right？
...lecher.
It was obvious... Okay, I'll meet you in the lobby, okay？
Hah～...
An open-air bath, huh！ It's nice outside after all...
Dear～？
What's the matter, ▲小早川＊▲！？
Rinko
Hehe, there's no one over here, I'm just saying.
They might be someone, you know...
Now, now！ What is that over there？ It's like a big cocoon.
Ah, is it really like that？
Oh, it was a sauna？ Rinko is going inside for a minute.
I see！ Should I come in too？
I have a question. When I go into the sauna, should I wrap a towel around me or something？
Towel？ No, I think that's okay, isn't it？
I see. Okay, I'll go in naked.
(I just imagined it...)
Rinko
We can't go in together, can we？ So I'm just going to pretend.
I see.
How's the hot water～？
